---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Scaffolding Staircase Tower Buyer's Guide | Prime Steel Tech">

<main class="bg-[#2b332a] min-h-screen pt-20 text-zinc-300">

  <section class="py-20 border-b border-white/5">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">

        <div>
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1541888946425-d81bb19240f5?q=80&w=1600"
            alt="Cuplock Scaffolding Staircase Tower"
            class="w-full h-[500px] object-cover rounded-sm border border-white/10 shadow-2xl"
          />
        </div>

        <div>

          <span class="inline-flex px-4 py-2 rounded-full border border-emerald-500/30 bg-emerald-500/10 text-emerald-400 uppercase tracking-widest text-xs font-bold mb-6">
             Buyer's Guide
          </span>

          <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-6xl font-black text-white uppercase leading-tight mb-8">
            What is a
            <span class="text-emerald-400">
              Staircase Tower?
            </span>
          </h1>

          <p class="font-jakarta text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed text-base mb-6">
            A Scaffolding Staircase Tower is a heavy-duty, modular vertical access system designed to provide safe, temporary passage for workers and materials between different structural levels. Utilizing high-strength medium-class steel pipes and advanced connection nodes, it ensures secure access on intensive job sites.
          </p>

          <p class="font-jakarta text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
            Engineered with an premium anti-skid dimple platform finish, full double-sided guardrails, and secure anchorage tie bars, our towers are optimized for superior load-bearing capacity and fast, tool-free assembly. They completely replace unsafe vertical ladders across construction, industrial, and offshore projects.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-8">
            <a
              href="/pdfs/Staircase-Buyers-Guide.pdf"
              download="Prime-Steel-Tech-Staircase-Tower-Datasheet.pdf"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 rounded-sm
              bg-emerald-500 px-8 py-4
              text-sm font-extrabold
              text-[#2b332a]
              hover:bg-emerald-400
              transition-all duration-300
              uppercase tracking-widest"
            >
              Download Datasheet PDF
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-10">

            <div class="bg-white/5 p-4 rounded-sm border border-white/10">
              <div class="text-emerald-400 font-bold">Anti-Skid Dimple</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-zinc-400 mt-1">
                Secure grip in wet & dusty conditions
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white/5 p-4 rounded-sm border border-white/10">
              <div class="text-emerald-400 font-bold">380 kg UDL</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-zinc-400 mt-1">
                Heavy-duty design platform capacity
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white/5 p-4 rounded-sm border border-white/10">
              <div class="text-emerald-400 font-bold">Full Fall Protection</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-zinc-400 mt-1">
                Guardrails & 150mm toe guards
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white/5 p-4 rounded-sm border border-white/10">
              <div class="text-emerald-400 font-bold">Dual Finish Protection</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-zinc-400 mt-1">
                Red-Oxide and Blue Enamel paint
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>


  <section class="py-20 bg-[#262d25]">

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4">

      <div class="text-center mb-14">

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-white uppercase">
          Why Choose Our
          <span class="text-emerald-400">Staircase Towers?</span>
        </h2>

        <div class="h-1 w-12 bg-emerald-400 mx-auto mt-5 rounded-full"></div>

      </div>

      <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 p-10 rounded-sm">

        <p class="font-jakarta text-zinc-300 text-base leading-loose">
          Prime Steel Tech Staircase Towers provide industry-leading structural stability and worker safety. Built with a specialized Cuplock node connection system, a single cup locks up to 4 ledgers simultaneously for incredibly fast, tool-free assembly. Every tower includes custom-engineered step arms with dimple-pressed anti-skid surfaces to prevent slips on-site. Equipped with double-sided handrails (top rails at 1,100 mm and mid-rails at 700 mm) alongside 150 mm high landing toe boards, these structures provide absolute edge protection. Backed by third-party ISO 9001 certifications, they offer premium, compliant safety standards that standard ladder systems simply cannot match.
        </p>

      </div>

    </div>

  </section>


  <section class="py-20">

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4">

      <div class="mb-10">

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-white uppercase">
          Prime Steel Tech
          <span class="text-emerald-400">
            Tower Specifications
          </span>
        </h2>

      </div>


      <div class="overflow-auto rounded-sm border border-white/10">

        <table class="w-full font-jakarta">

          <thead class="bg-emerald-500/10">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left text-emerald-400 uppercase text-xs">
                Parameter
              </th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left text-emerald-400 uppercase text-xs">
                General Specification
              </th>
            </tr>
          </thead>

          <tbody class="divide-y divide-white/5">

            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">Primary Material</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">M.S. (IS 1161 Grade YST210) / Medium Class Pipe</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">Tube Outer Diameter</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">48.3 mm</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">Platform Height / Overall Tower Height</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">6,000 mm / 7,500 mm (incl. top rail)</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">Stair Width & Material</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">≥ 1,000 mm clear / M.S. Dimple Plate</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">Platform Design Load (UDL)</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">380 kg (3.73 kN/m² | 75.7 psf)</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">Surface Protection Finish</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">Red-Oxide + Blue Enamel Paint</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">Components & Locking Type</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">Drop-Forged Steel Top Cup / Pressed Metal Bottom Cup</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">Regulatory Compliance</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">IS 1161, IS 3696, IS 4014, EN 12811-1, BS 1139-3, OSHA</td>
            </tr>

          </tbody>

        </table>

      </div>

    </div>

  </section>


  <section class="py-20 bg-[#262d25]">

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4">

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-white mb-10 uppercase">
        Available Tower
        <span class="text-emerald-400">
          Configurations
        </span>
      </h2>


      <div class="overflow-auto rounded-sm border border-white/10">

        <table class="w-full font-jakarta">

          <thead class="bg-emerald-500/10">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left text-emerald-400 uppercase text-xs">Configuration Parameter</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left text-emerald-400 uppercase text-xs">PSST-4 System</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left text-emerald-400 uppercase text-xs">PSST-8 System</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>

          <tbody class="divide-y divide-white/5">

            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-bold text-white">Number of Vertical Legs</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">4 Legs</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">8 Legs</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-bold text-white">Grid Layout Size (L x W)</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">2,500 x 2,000 mm</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">2,000 x 3,800 mm</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-bold text-white">Staircase Step Rise</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">214 mm (Class-B EN 12811-1)</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">187.5 mm (Class-B EN 12811-1)</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-bold text-white">Staircase Pitch/Angle</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">49° Angle</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">50° Angle</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-bold text-white">Landing Platform Depth</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">600 mm (in direction of travel)</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">800 mm (in direction of travel)</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-bold text-white">Landing Platform Width</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">2,000 mm</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4">2,000 mm</td>
            </tr>

          </tbody>

        </table>

      </div>

    </div>

  </section>


  <section class="py-20">

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4">

      <div class="text-center mb-14">

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-white uppercase">
          Factors to Consider Before Buying
          <span class="text-emerald-400">
            Staircase Towers
          </span>
        </h2>

      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6 mt-12">

        <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-sm p-8 hover:border-emerald-500/40 transition-all">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3 uppercase">
            01. Grid Size & Layout Constraints
          </h3>
          <p class="font-jakarta text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
            Assess the space limitations of your job site. The 4-leg configuration (PSST-4) utilizes a 2,500 x 2,000 mm footprint which is ideal for tight structural spacing, whereas the heavy-duty 8-leg configuration (PSST-8) requires a wider 2,000 x 3,800 mm footprint.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-sm p-8 hover:border-emerald-500/40 transition-all">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3 uppercase">
            02. Height & Anchorage Requirements
          </h3>
          <p class="font-jakarta text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
            Ensure your configuration aligns with standard heights or requests customized extensions. Remember that structural tie bars are mandatory once the total tower height exceeds 3 times the least base dimension, with specific wall attachment rules up to 4 m vertically.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-sm p-8 hover:border-emerald-500/40 transition-all">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3 uppercase">
            03. Uniformly Distributed Load (UDL)
          </h3>
          <p class="font-jakarta text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
            Evaluate the density of worker traffic and tool transportation. Prime Steel Tech towers feature a high platform UDL of 380 kg (3.73 kN/m²), strictly meeting Class-B global standard compliance for multi-worker movement.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-sm p-8 hover:border-emerald-500/40 transition-all">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3 uppercase">
            04. Compliance & On-Site Legislation
          </h3>
          <p class="font-jakarta text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
            Verify that your safety code mandates align with local regulations. These towers conform strictly to regional Indian Standards (IS 3696/4014) mandated under the BOCW Act 1996, alongside global standardizations including EN 12811-1 and US OSHA.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>

  </section>



  <section class="py-20 bg-[#262d25]">

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4">

      <h2 class="text-3xl text-center font-black text-white uppercase mb-16">
        Industries Using
        <span class="text-emerald-400">
          Staircase Towers
        </span>
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-6">

        <div class="bg-white/5 p-8 border border-white/10 rounded-sm">
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-3">Civil Infrastructure</h3>
          <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm">
            High-rise residential builds, bridges, flyovers, and metro viaduct networks.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white/5 p-8 border border-white/10 rounded-sm">
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-3">Heavy Industrial Plants</h3>
          <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm">
            Refineries, petrochemical processing zones, cement factories, and power hubs.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white/5 p-8 border border-white/10 rounded-sm">
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-3">Marine Fabrication</h3>
          <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm">
            Ship construction, shipyard maintenance, dockyard works, and offshore platforms.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white/5 p-8 border border-white/10 rounded-sm">
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-3">Specialized Sectors</h3>
          <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm">
            Nuclear energy sites, defence structures, and aircraft hangar staging.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>

  </section>

</main>

</Layout>


<style is:global>
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Plus+Jakarta+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap');
.font-jakarta {
  font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;
}
</style>